It is in the northwestern part of the country, bordering Algeria and the Mediterranean Sea. It covers an area of 3,102 km². As of the 2014 census, 401,477 people lived there. Census 2014 (National Institute of Statistics) The capital is Jendouba. == References == Category:1956 establishments in Tunisia Category:Governorates of Tunisia
